Then, you will develop an execution timeline that handles competing priorities, communicate a product roadmap that builds consensus amongst internal stakeholders, and create a comprehensive go-to-market plan based on product KPIs. Finally, you will build tests to enhance product features based on market data.

Finally, you’ll learn how to turn your low-fidelity prototype into a high-fidelity design, and improve its performance based on data.
